<hl>
<seg id=1> Russian Prime Minister talked about the economic situation </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, Moscow, January 8th- Today at a government meeting, Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Cheromeijing said that, the major achievement that Russia made in 1997 was to create the fundamental premise for economic growth. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to the report of Tass, a Russian news agency, Mikhail Cheromeijing said that, compared to 1996, the domestic gross product of Russia during the last year increased 1.2%, the industrial gross product increased 3.2%, the retail gross product increased 3.9%, the rate of annual inflation was 11%, which was half what it was in 1996, and residents' incomes increased 2.5%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Meanwhile, Mikhail Cheromeijing also pointed out that, there were also quite a few problems that existed inside the country last year, for example, the tax revenue had a poor performance; the investment plans were not achieved; the favorable trade balance decreased; The financial measures that the government adopted did not work, etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> While talking about the work needed to be done for this year, Mikhail Cheromeijing said that, the new draft plan for structure reform and economic development is being prepared for submittal to the government extensible meeting for discussion, which will be held on February 26th. </seg>
<seg id=6> According to this plan, Russian domestic gross products should increase 2% next year, and the rate of inflation would drop down between 5% and 8%. </seg>
</p>
